      "statePolicyText": {
        "markup": "<p><strong>California:</strong> In California, travel time that exceeds normal commute and occurs under the direction of the employer must generally be paid. This includes travel to remote job sites or for training, regardless of time of day.</p>\n<p><strong>Illinois:</strong> Illinois generally follows FLSA guidelines but requires compensable travel time to be reflected on pay stubs as part of total hours worked. Consult HR for reporting assistance if needed.</p>",
